## Setup (no local patching)
- ethereum-package: `ethpandaops/ethereum-package@5ff8db70` — official #1432 ("set --builder-api-url per instance")
- buildoor image: `ethpandaops/buildoor:main` (devnet-5 spec + --extra-data, both merged upstream)
- prysm: gcr.io/offchainlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:latest (c80ca9986055) (carries the `Builder bid fan-out` log)
- two buildoors on participant 1 (lodestar): `buildoor-lodestar-nethermind-1-1` and `-1-2`

## What this proves
prysm queries ALL configured builders in parallel, receives a bid from each, selects one,
and that builder's payload is included on-chain. Both builders win (bids are tied, so the
tie-break falls to whichever builder responds first in the fan-out).

## 1. Each buildoor has its OWN --builder-api-url (per-instance, official #1432 launcher)
```
buildoor-1-1: --builder-api-url=http://buildoor-lodestar-nethermind-1-1:8080
buildoor-1-2: --builder-api-url=http://buildoor-lodestar-nethermind-1-2:8080
```

## 2. prysm — fan-out: received 2 bids from BOTH builders (one line per proposal)
```
